<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1969,2034]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,255]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1969,1995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Body long, slender, densely papillate; with two longitudinal rows of macro- and two rows of microtubercles, macro- and micropapillae with terminal papillae. Anterior end with a median antenna and two pairs of lateral antennae. Eyes present or absent. Proboscis long, cylindrical. Parapodia uniramous. First chaetiger with recurved hooks; following chaetigers uniramous, with simple chaetae and compound falcigers. Pygidium 
<emphasis box="[272,323,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">with</emphasis>
or without 
<emphasis box="[459,695,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">four macrotubercles</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
